The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 17: Air Deccan will tap the market with its initial public offering (IPO) between November and January, offering a 20-25 per cent stake, the airline chief G.R. Gopinath said. Four merchant bankers, who were not associated with the Jet Airways IPO, will be appointed soon, he added. Air Deccan will get five more ATR turbo-prop aircraft and seven Airbus A-320s this fiscal. It will get another seven A-320s next year.

 New Delhi, Aug. 17: The Centre will propose exemption of perishable processed food items from the value-added tax net at the empowered committees meeting to be held here on August 24. It will also favour a 1-4 per cent tax on the non-perishable items.

 New Delhi, Aug. 17: A dozen banks and financial institutions are joining hands to build a consortium for funding power sector projects. The consortium includes Power Finance Corporation, Life Insurance Corporation, Punjab National Bank, Oriental Bank of Commerce, Bank of Baroda, Canara Bank and Corporation Bank.

 Mumbai, Aug. 17: The debt recovery tribunal (DRT) has ordered tainted broker Ketan Parekh and his group of companies to pay Rs 124 crore with interest, aggregating Rs 207 crore, to Bank of India (BoI) on account of Rs 137-crore pay-order scam that affected the bank.

 New Delhi, Aug. 17: Sharp differences have surfaced between the Tatas and the government on rights over surplus land lying with their joint venture, Videsh Sanchar Nigam Ltd (VSNL). 

 Mumbai, Aug. 17: Birla Power Solutions Ltd will raise Rs 50 crore through rights/public issue subject to shareholders? approval and necessary permissions from appropriate authorities..

 New Delhi, Aug. 17: The fleet acquisition plan of Indian Airlines (IA) worth Rs 10,237 crore will be taken up by the cabinet committee on economic affairs next week.




